'''Peter Allen David''' ([[September 23]], [[1950s#1956|1956]] - [[May 24]], [[2025]]) was an [[Wikipedia:United States|American]] writer, who wrote "[[Skippy the Jedi Droid]]" for the [[Star Wars Tales 1|first issue]] of ''[[Star Wars Tales]]''. he also wrote the teen spy adventure [[Wikipedia:SpyBoy|''SpyBoy'']] for [[Dark Horse Comics]], but his best-known comic work was on [[Wikipedia:The Incredible Hulk (Comic series)|''The Incredible Hulk'']]. David was also known for writing various [[Wikipedia:Star Trek|''Star Trek'']] novels, including the original ''[[Wikipedia:Star Trek: New Frontier|Star Trek: New Frontier]]'' series. He often jokingly described his occupation as "Writer of Stuff". 

Other [[Marvel Comics]] titles he wrote for included ''Spider-Man, Spider-Man 2099, X-Factor, Fantastic Four, Captain Marvel, Scarlet Spider,'' and the adaptation of Stephen King's ''The Dark Tower.'' He also wrote for ''Halo: Helljumper'' and the [[2011]] video game ''Spider-Man: Edge of Time.'' At [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]], David wrote for ''Aquaman, Young Justice, Supergirl,'' and ''Fallen Angel,'' as well as a few episodes of [[Cartoon Network]]'s ''Young Justice'' cartoon adaptation''.'' He also wrote for other TV shows and video games, namely ''Babylon 5, Ben 10: Alien Force.''

David also co-created the kids' sci-fi series ''[[Wikipedia:Space Cases|Space Cases]]'' for [[Wikipedia:Nickelodeon|Nickelodeon]] in the 1990s, which guest-starred actors such as ''Star Wars'' legend [[Mark Hamill]] and future ''Star Wars'' voice actor [[George Takei]].

